'''Onta-mai''' (御田舞) * {{ill|Hanazono Onta-mai|ja|花園の御田舞|12=draft}} - A folk performance from Hanazono Yanase, {{ill|Katsuragi, Wakayama|ja|かつらぎ町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ito District, Wakayama|ja|伊都郡|12=draft}}, Wakayama Prefecture. Designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Japan. * {{ill|Suginohara Onta-mai|ja|杉野原の御田舞|12=draft}} - A folk performance from Suginohara, {{ill|Aridagawa, Wakayama|ja|有田川町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Arida District, Wakayama|ja|有田郡|12=draft}}, Wakayama Prefecture. Designated as an Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property of Japan. * {{ill|Nihiyama Shrine Onta-mai|ja|仁比山神社の御田舞|12=draft}} - A folk performance from {{ill|Kanzaki, Saga|ja|神埼市|12=draft}}, Kanzaki Town, Saga Prefecture. Designated as a Prefectural Intangible Cultural Property. See {{ill|Nihiyama Shrine|ja|仁比山神社|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Azayama Shrine Onta-mai|ja|四阿屋神社の御田舞|12=draft}} - A folk performance from Kuraue Town, {{ill|Tosu, Saga|ja|鳥栖市|12=draft}}, Saga Prefecture. Designated as a Prefectural Intangible Cultural Property. See {{ill|Azayama Shrine|ja|四阿屋神社|12=draft}}. == See Also == * {{ill|Onta|ja|御田|1=Sacred rice field|12=draft}}, {{ill|Ta-asobi|ja|田遊び|12=draft}}
